<paragraph id="6C7336F0455CA55EDC3AFA2C643CF9B4" blockId="4.[843,1497,1449,1639]" pageId="4" pageNumber="377">
<emphasis id="5EB8EAE2455CA55EDC3AFA2C63FAFA12" box="[881,1014,1449,1473]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="377">Etymology.–</emphasis>
The species is named in honour of Albert II de 
<collectingCountry id="14DB7660455CA55EDC27FA4F63CBFA31" box="[876,967,1482,1506]" name="Monaco" pageId="4" pageNumber="377">Monaco</collectingCountry>
, Albert Alexandre Louis Pierre Grimaldi, Prince of 
<collectingCountry id="14DB7660455CA55EDC22FA6E63CFF9D0" box="[873,963,1515,1539]" name="Monaco" pageId="4" pageNumber="377">Monaco</collectingCountry>
, in recognition of his tireless support to the NGO Fanamby for their conservation activities in Northern 
<collectingCountry id="14DB7660455CA55EDAC4F9886381F995" name="Madagascar" pageId="4" pageNumber="377">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, especially in the Andrafiamena region where the species seems to be endemic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C7336F0455CA55EDC3AF9FD64ECF8E4" blockId="4.[843,1494,1656,1847]" pageId="4" pageNumber="377">
<emphasis id="5EB8EAE2455CA55EDC3AF9FD65B6F943" box="[881,1466,1656,1680]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="377">
Distribution and ecology. – 
<taxonomicName id="ABCC4D73455CA55EDBE8F9FD65B6F943" box="[1187,1466,1656,1680]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Exacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="377" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alberti-grimaldii">Exacum alberti-grimaldii</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is only known from the Ampantsona river watershed occurring on seeping sandstone outcrops or on temporary humid river banks in semi-deciduous or sclerophyllous forest. It is an annual species completing its life-cycle in less than two and half months between March and May.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C7336F0455CA55FDC3AF8CD62FCFE62" blockId="4.[843,1493,1864,1955]" lastBlockId="5.[103,754,280,856]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="378" pageId="4" pageNumber="377">
<emphasis id="5EB8EAE2455CA55EDC3AF8CD6560F8B3" box="[881,1388,1864,1888]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="377">
Conservation status. – 
<taxonomicName id="ABCC4D73455CA55EDB14F8CD6560F8B3" box="[1119,1388,1864,1888]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Exacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="377" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alberti-grimaldii">Exacum alberti-grimaldii</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has been observed only three times in the Ampantsona valley and collected only once. With only one collection and three known subpopulations, an AOO of&gt; 
<quantity id="AB349B15455DA55FDEE8FE9C61D4FEE2" box="[419,472,281,305]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" unit="km" value="9.0">9 km</quantity>
<superScript id="9BB99BB8455DA55FDE9CFE9D61D3FEF5" attach="left" box="[471,479,280,294]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">2</superScript>
within the Protected Area under creation of Andrafiamena-Andavakoera and according to its annual life-cycle and rarity of proper habitats, 
<emphasis id="5EB8EAE2455DA55FDDCEFEDC60C7FE42" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">E.albertigrimaldii</emphasis>
is assigned a preliminary status of Vulnerable (VU D2) following IUCN Categories and Criteria (
<bibRefCitation id="085D4B01455DA55FDD12FE1C62E8FE62" author="IUCN" box="[601,740,409,433]" firstAuthor="IUCN" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" refId="ref2412" refString="IUCN (2001). Categories and Criteria (version 3.1). IUCN, Gland and Cambridge." type="book" year="2001">IUCN, 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C7336F0455DA55FDFC7FE4561D7FC8B" blockId="5.[103,754,280,856]" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">
<emphasis id="5EB8EAE2455DA55FDFC7FE4560E6FE0B" box="[140,234,448,472]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">Notes. –</emphasis>
Only two other species are characterized by verticillated upper leaves and umbella-shape inflorescence: 
<taxonomicName id="ABCC4D73455DA55FDF2CFD856170FDCB" authority="Klack." authorityName="Klack." box="[103,380,512,536]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Exacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dolichantherum">
<emphasis id="5EB8EAE2455DA55FDF2CFD856124FDCB" box="[103,296,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">E.dolichantherum</emphasis>
Klack.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="5EB8EAE2455DA55FDEE4FD856236FDCB" box="[431,570,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">E.nossibense</emphasis>
Klack. (
<bibRefCitation id="085D4B01455DA55FDDD6FD85612BFDEB" author="KLACKENBERG, J." firstAuthor="KLACKENBERG" journalOrPublisher="Opera Bot." page="94" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" pagination="1 - 144" part="84" refId="ref2431" refString="KLACKENBERG, J. (1985). The genus Exacum (Gentianaceae). Opera Bot. 84: 1 - 144." title="The genus Exacum (Gentianaceae)" type="journal article" year="1985">KLACKENBERG, 1985: 94</bibRefCitation>
; Fig. 69, 96, 71). 
<taxonomicName id="ABCC4D73455DA55FDEA8FDA562FDFDEB" box="[483,753,544,568]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Exacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alberti-grimaldii">
<emphasis id="5EB8EAE2455DA55FDEA8FDA562FDFDEB" box="[483,753,544,568]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">Exacum alberti-grimaldii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="ABCC4D73455DA55FDE9CFDC562ADFD8B" box="[471,673,576,600]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Exacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dolichantherum">
<emphasis id="5EB8EAE2455DA55FDE9CFDC562ADFD8B" box="[471,673,576,600]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">E.dolichantherum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its smaller discrete petals (2-3 Χ 1.0- 
<quantity id="AB349B15455DA55FDE97FDE56223FDAB" box="[476,559,608,632]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
vs 3-7 Χ 
<quantity id="AB349B15455DA55FDDD0FDE562FDFDAB" box="[667,753,608,632]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2-4 mm</quantity>
for 
<taxonomicName id="ABCC4D73455DA55FDFD8FD05616DFD4B" box="[147,353,640,664]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Exacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dolichantherum">
<emphasis id="5EB8EAE2455DA55FDFD8FD05616DFD4B" box="[147,353,640,664]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">E. dolichantherum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and from 
<emphasis id="5EB8EAE2455DA55FDEB9FD056299FD4B" box="[498,661,640,664]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">E. nossibensee</emphasis>
by the absence of wings on the sepals (
<figureCitation id="F4F72A75455DA55FDE83FD256228FD6B" box="[456,548,672,696]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStart-2="Fig" captionStartId-0="2.[118,143,1877,1897]" captionStartId-1="3.[103,128,1900,1920]" captionStartId-2="4.[118,143,1344,1364]" captionTargetBox-0="[118,1494,281,1856]" captionTargetBox-1="[103,1479,280,1881]" captionTargetBox-2="[117,1494,280,1328]" captionTargetId-0="figure-19@2.[151,1460,294,1843]" captionTargetId-1="figure-37@3.[101,1479,279,1882]" captionTargetId-2="figure-299@4.[117,1494,280,1328]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionTargetPageId-2="4" captionText-0="Fig. 2. – Exacum alberti-grimaldii Wohlh. &amp; Callm. A. Habitus of a multi-umbellated individual; B. Flower; C. Habitus of an individual with single umbel; D. Stamen; E. Flower with calyx removed; F. Detail of an autogamous flower. [Wohlhauser &amp; Bongary 803, G, TAN] [Drawing: Roger Lala Andriamiarisoa]" captionText-1="Fig. 3. – Flowering plant of Exacum alberti-grimaldii Wohlh. &amp; Callm. with detail of a flower (framed). [Wohlhauser &amp; Bongary 803] [Photo: S. Wohlhauser]" captionText-2="Fig. 4. – An autogamous flower of Exacum alberti-grimaldii Wohlh. &amp; Callm. showing the unwinged sepals. [Wohlhauser &amp; Bongary 803] [Photo: S. Wohlhauser]" figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5851616" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5851618" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5851620" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5851616/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5851618/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/5851620/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">Fig. 2-4</figureCitation>
). The new species grows in a dry transition area on diverse substrates (limestone-sandstone) whereas 
<taxonomicName id="ABCC4D73455DA55FDECEFD656244FD2B" box="[389,584,736,760]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Exacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="378" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dolichantherum">
<emphasis id="5EB8EAE2455DA55FDECEFD656244FD2B" box="[389,584,736,760]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">E.dolichantherum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows in open areas on sand along the littoral of the east coast and 
<emphasis id="5EB8EAE2455DA55FDDEFFC8560CDFCEB" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">E.nossibensee</emphasis>
is endemic from the Sambirano Domain 
<emphasis id="5EB8EAE2455DA55FDD3FFCA562A3FCEB" box="[628,687,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="378">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="085D4B01455DA55FDDFEFCA560E5FC8B" author="HUMBERT, H." journalOrPublisher="Annee Biol." pageId="5" pageNumber="378" pagination="439 - 448" part="31" refId="ref2389" refString="HUMBERT, H. (1955). Les territoires phytogeographiques de Madagascar. Annee Biol. 31: 439 - 448." title="Les territoires phytogeographiques de Madagascar" type="journal article" year="1955">HUMBERT (1955)</bibRefCitation>
on diverse substrates.
</paragraph>
